import {useEffect, useState} from "react"; import axios from "axios"; export default function ProductList(props) { const [products,setProducts] =useState([]); useEffect(()=>{ axios.get('http://localhost:8080/api/products').then(c =>{ setProducts(c.data) }) },[]) return( <>

LIST PRODUCT

{products.map((c,count =0)=> ( ) )}
STT NAME PRICE PRICE SALE CATEGORY VIEW PURCHASE STATUS TIME MAKE IMG ACTION
{count +1} {c.name} {c.price} {c.priceSale} {c.category.name} {c.view} {c.purchase} {c.status} {c.timeMake} {c.image}
) }
